---
alwaysApply: true
---

<git_commit_strategy>
<system_rules>
- Spec: Conventional Commits
- Output Language: Korean (Description ONLY)
- Description Rule: Noun-phrase termination ONLY (e.g., ~구현, ~수정, ~추가, ~제거)
</system_rules>

<format>
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body explaining WHY, not how]
</format>

<constraints>
- Max Length: Subject line <= 50 characters
- Spacing: Exactly one space after colon (e.g., `feat: 메시지`)
- No Period: Never end subject line with a period (`.`)
- Monorepo Scope: Always specify package/domain as scope (e.g., `backend`, `frontend`, `auth`)
</constraints>

<types>
feat: New feature
fix: Bug fix
docs: Documentation changes
style: Code formatting/linting (no logic change)
refactor: Code restructuring (no fix/feature)
test: Adding/modifying tests
ci: CI/CD workflows, build scripts (GitHub Actions)
chore: Build tasks, pnpm, tool configs (.eslintrc, .cursorrules)
perf: Performance improvement
</types>

<anti_patterns>
- DO NOT use past tense verbs (❌ ~했습니다, ~했음, ~완료)
- DO NOT use English in <description>
- DO NOT use broad scopes (❌ feat(code): 관련 수정)
</anti_patterns>

<few_shot_examples>
feat(backend): JWT 기반 액세스 토큰 발급 기능 구현
fix(frontend): 모바일 뷰 결제 버튼 미정렬 오류 수정
docs: README 문서에 테스트 전략 가이드라인 추가
refactor(auth): 중복 회원 검증 로직을 커스텀 가드로 분리
test(lecture): 강의 수정 기능 통합 테스트 코드 추가
chore(root): pnpm 워크스페이스 패키지 의존성 최적화
</few_shot_examples>
</git_commit_strategy>
